Method Detail

pull

public abstract void pull()
The MessagingService contacts the remote centralized Messaging service to retrieve any new messages. The message will still be kept on the remote service after this retrieval. This method returns nothing, the NetworkingService will inform the MessagingService when it receives the reply from the remote service.

sendInvitation

public abstract void sendInvitation(User invitedUser,
                                    java.lang.String content)
Sends an invitation message to another user and also stores it in the Mailbox. The message will be sent to the remote Messaging Service, which will store it in the destination user's mailbox.

Parameters:
invitedUser - - the invited user
content - - the String containing the invitation's text message written by the user for the invited user

sendInvitation

public abstract void sendInvitation(java.lang.String externalPersonEmail,
                                    java.lang.String content)
Sends an invitation message to an external person and also stores it in the Mailbox. The message will be sent to the remote Messaging Service, which will send an invitation email message to the external person.

Parameters:
externalPersonEmail - - the external person's email address
content - - the String containing the invitation's text message written by the user for the invited person
